# Frontend Community UX

- Design clear public vs member-only journeys; avoid ambiguous CTAs.
- Show graceful auth prompts when library actions require sign-in.
- Never rely on hidden buttons as security; backend must enforce access.
- Keep article listing pages fast, searchable, and SEO-friendly.
- Use reusable components for cards, filters, and content states.
- Handle loading, empty, and error states on all data-driven screens.
- Keep copy explicit for library restrictions and registration benefits.
- Preserve accessibility: semantic markup, keyboard flow, contrast, labels.
- Ensure responsive behavior for mobile-first university audiences.
